Posted on: 29 Apr 2014
THE ROLE
Expand all
Position: Business Development Manager
Overview:
We’re looking to expand our young, dynamic and active team in Dubai, looking after our business in the Middle East. You are an experienced and energetic sales person, hungry for new challenges. You are Internet savvy, knowing the latest technologies and trends in the market. You enjoy meeting new people, learn new technologies and challenge yourself every day. Value selling is familiar to you and you believe in building long term relationships.
At Liana Technologies, the Business Development Manager manages the whole customer lifecycle from new business acquisition to training, support and account management. It’s a multitasking role, which makes it event more fun, challenging and rewarding. Arabic language skill is a plus.
Essential Job Functions:
•	Responsible for heading up expansion in new channels as well as continued expansion among existing clients
•	Building relationships with existing clients in an attempt to increase their current spend
•	You will be instrumental in devising and implementing the strategy for meeting sales performance targets
•	Following up new business opportunities and setting up meetings by cold calling
•	Communicating new product developments to prospective clients
•	Providing management with feedback
•	Screens potential business deals by analyzing market strategies, deal requirements, potential, and financials; evaluating options; resolving internal priorities; recommending equity investments.
•	Closes new business deals by coordinating requirements; developing and negotiating contracts; integrating contract requirements with business operations.
•	Updates job knowledge by participating in educational opportunities; reading professional publications; maintaining personal networks; participating in professional organizations.
•	Enhances organization reputation by accepting ownership for accomplishing new and different requests; exploring opportunities to add value to job accomplishments.
REQUIREMENTS
Requirements, Skills/Abilities:
•	3+ years preferably in the online, media and marketing industry
•	Proven track record in sales, business development and winning new business
•	Proven track record of increasing revenue through generation of leads
•	Show an understanding of the challenges facing the industry at present and illustrate a knowledge of the operational attention to detail that will be required to succeed within the industry
•	Not afraid of a phone
•	Good business sense
•	Entrepreneurial attitude
•	Plenty of initiative
•	Motivation for sales
•	Prospecting skills
•	Sales planning and negotiation skills
•	Internet savvy (need to understand the basics of how internet works)
•	Hardcore sales professional
•	Car and valid UAE driving license – as will be required to attend business meetings
Reporting to: General Manager
Key Contacts: Directors, Managers, Personnel, Clients
Qualification: B.Sc or higher
Languages: Excellent command of English
Location: Dubai
Working Conditions: 5 days per week
Salary: Base + uncapped commission + benefits
About Liana Technologies:
Liana Technologies is an active and agile company specialized in digital marketing and communication software. Our clients are professionals in digital marketing, communications and advertisement - our mission is to give them the best possible tools in the form of digital Liana product family. Liana Technologies has the office in Dubai where the Middle East business is run from.
ABOUT THE COMPANY
Offshore Recruitment Services specialise in the recruitment of in all aspects of offshore vacancies for all levels of permanent, temporary and contract positions.
Whether a client is searching for a highly skilled candidate, looking to head hunt a specific individual, a team of contractors for a project or management of gifted personnel, we are ready and have a proven track record of meeting such requirements.
Offshore Recruitment Services was formed with the specific aim of providing a quality service to link key candidates to our clients. We find the right people for your business.
